        <num>CC 2017</num>
        <heading>2017.  Express dissolution clause</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2017.  Express dissolution clause
The parties may expressly agree that the contract shall be dissolved for the failure to perform a particular obligation.  In that case, the contract is deemed dissolved at the time it provides for or, in the absence of such a provision, at the time the obligee gives notice to the obligor that he avails himself of the dissolution clause.</p>
        </content>
